  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d85\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dc5\u0dad\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Even if the state ministers are appointed, there is no allocation of money",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported through the sources of the ruling party that the appointment of state ministers is likely to take place tomorrow (6th). Accordingly, about 35 state ministers are to be appointed and it is reported that the party has submitted to the President a list of the names of the MPs nominated by the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna for the position of state ministers.",
        "It is stated that although the State Ministers are appointed, it has been decided not to gazette their respective scopes this time and that the State Minister should work under the Ministry belonging to his Cabinet Minister.",
        "It is reported that a Secretary of the State Ministry will be appointed, but it is planned not to make a separate allocation of money for the State Ministry, and to carry out the activities of the State Ministry under the Ministry's budget.",
        "Government sources also state that the appointment of a permanent cabinet will be delayed for another seven to two years.",
        "According to government sources, the opposition to some of the names submitted by the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna for cabinet ministerships has caused the delay in the appointment of this cabinet.",
        "However, it is reported that there will be no change in the positions of the current 18 ministers and only new cabinet ministers will join the cabinet."
      ],
